<p>An appeals court in Bogotá struck down former president Álvaro Uribe&#x27;s convictions for bribery and witness tampering, revoking the 12‑year house arrest sentence he received in August 2025 [reuters.com#1][bbc.com#1][france24.com#1]. The ruling removes the immediate criminal restrictions on Uribe but does not close the legal saga: further challenges and appeals remain possible and the case could still move through higher courts [reuters.com#1][straitstimes.com#1]. The decision was widely reported across international outlets as a major procedural turn in a long-running trial that drew substantive evidence and months of courtroom scrutiny [france24.com#1][scmp.com#1].</p><h3>Highlights:</h3><ul><li>Historical first: Uribe&#x27;s August conviction had marked the first time a former Colombian president was criminally convicted, making the overturning a reversal of a historic verdict [bbc.com#1][france24.com#1]</li><li>Allegations background: Prosecutors had accused Uribe of attempting to influence witnesses who alleged he had ties to far‑right paramilitary groups in the 1990s, material presented during a nearly six‑month trial [scmp.com#1][france24.com#1]</li><li>Outstanding legal issues: Reuters reports parts of the broader case remain unresolved, with the court still considering appeals related to a separate fraud charge [reuters.com#1]</li></ul><h3>Perspectives:</h3><ul><li>Álvaro Uribe: Uribe has denied any wrongdoing throughout the proceedings, rejecting the accusations against him. (<a href='https://www.scmp.com/news/world/americas/article/3329857/colombia-court-overturns-ex-president-uribes-conviction-bribery-and-witness-tampering'>South China Morning Post</a>)</li><li>Prosecutors: Prosecutors said they presented evidence that Uribe tried to influence witnesses who accused him of links to paramilitary groups. (<a href='https://www.france24.com/en/video/20251022-colombian-court-overturns-ex-president-uribe-s-fraud-and-witness-tampering-conviction'>France 24</a>)</li><li>Senator involved in case: A senator involved in the proceedings said he will appeal the acquittal, a step that could bring the matter to Colombia&#x27;s Supreme Court. (<a href='https://www.straitstimes.com/world/Colombia-ex-president-acquitted-in-witness-tampering-case-senator-to-appeal'>The Straits Times</a>)</li></ul><h3>Sources:</h3><ul><li><a href='https://www.straitstimes.com/world/Colombia-ex-president-acquitted-in-witness-tampering-case-senator-to-appeal'>Colombia ex-president acquitted in witness tampering case, senator to appeal</a> - straitstimes.com</li><li><a href='https://www.france24.com/en/video/20251022-colombian-court-overturns-ex-president-uribe-s-fraud-and-witness-tampering-conviction'>Colombian court overturns ex-president Uribe&#x27;s fraud and witness tampering conviction</a> - france24.com</li><li><a href='https://en.mercopress.com/2025/10/22/colombia-uribe-acquitted-by-bogota-court-citing-procedural-glitches'>Colombia: Uribe acquitted by Bogotá court citing procedural glitches</a> - mercopress.com</li><li><a href='https://www.scmp.com/news/world/americas/article/3329857/colombia-court-overturns-ex-president-uribes-conviction-bribery-and-witness-tampering'>Colombia court overturns Uribe’s conviction for bribery, witness tampering</a> - scmp.com</li><li><a href='https://www.bbc.com/news/articles/c629zz8gz5mo'>Colombian court overturns former president&#x27;s conviction</a> - bbc.com</li><li><a href='https://www.reuters.com/world/americas/colombian-court-strikes-down-former-presidents-bribery-conviction-2025-10-21/'>A court in Colombia overturns a bribery conviction against former President Álvaro Uribe, who had been sentenced to 12 years of house arrest in August 2025. The court is still considering further appeals on a fraud charge. (Reuters)</a> - reuters.com</li></ul>